main event: Two bright objects were observed climbing rapidly in the sky in Teaticket, Massachusetts.
interesting points: The objects were initially described as illuminated airplanes but were later determined to be unidentified., Observers noted that the objects changed course and speed suddenly., The sighting included a group with backgrounds in aviation and military experience., The objects were seen about 20 degrees above the eastern horizon., Witnesses reported that the lights appeared to scatter in different directions before disappearing behind a cloud.
witness description: LTC Garner, Marvin Roger Odom (owner of Falmouth Airport), LT Phillip Wood, and John Roger Gustafson Jr.
